Package biolockj.exception

This package contains Exception subclasses specific to BioLockJ.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    FatalExceptionHandler
    FatalExceptionHandler saves logs somewhere the user can access if failures occur before the log file is generated.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    BioLockJException
    Superclass for all BioLockJ exception used to ensure message uniformity.
    BioLockJStatusException  
    ConfigException
    ConfigException is the superclass for all BioLockJ configuration file Exceptions used to ensure message uniformity.
    ConfigFormatException
    ConfigFormatException is thrown if property is defined but the format is invalid.
    ConfigNotFoundException
    ConfigNotFoundException is thrown if a required Config property is undefined.
    ConfigPathException
    ConfigPathException is thrown if property is invalid file paths are encountered when processing the BioLockJ configuration file.
    ConfigViolationException
    ConfigViolationException is thrown at runtime due to application state violations caused by invalid module I/O (sequences or metadata) as defined by Config properties.
    DirectModuleException
    Some module are run as secondary instances of the BioLockJ program.
    DockerVolCreationException  
    DockerVolumeException  
    ExpectationFileFormatException
    TODO : Add info
    MetadataException
    MetadataException is thrown if errors occur processing Metadata files.
    OtuFileException
    OtuFileException is thrown if errors occur processing OTU files.
    PipelineFormationException
    PipelineFormationException is thrown when there is a problem in setting up the modules to run.
    PipelineScriptException
    PipelineScriptException is thrown by BashScriptBuilder if errors occur writing MASTER & WORKER scripts.
    RuntimeParamException
    ConfigException is the superclass for all BioLockJ configuration file Exceptions used to ensure message uniformity.
    SequnceFormatException
    SequnceFormatException is thrown if errors occur processing fasta/fastq sequence files.
    SpecialPropertiesException
    This type of exception is thrown if an error occurs while processing a special type of property such as "exe." properties or defaultProps.
    ValidationException
    ValidationException is thrown at module runtime if the Validation module finds a discrepancy between the expectations given for one or more files and the files found in the previous module.
    ValidationExecutionException
    ValidationException is thrown at module runtime if the ValidationUtil throws a non-BioLockJ error while validating module output.
    ValidationUtilityException
